25|$|In 2001, NASA's Mars Odyssey orbiter {{arrived at}} Mars. Its {{mission is to}} use spectrometers and imagers to hunt for {{evidence}} of past or present water and volcanic activity on Mars. In 2002, {{it was announced that}} the probe's <b>gamma</b> <b>ray</b> <b>spectrometer</b> and neutron spectrometer had detected large amounts of hydrogen, indicating that there are vast deposits of water ice in the upper three meters of Mars' soil within 60° latitude of the south pole.|$|E
