40|$|Digital pulse {{processing}} (DPP) systems, {{based on}} direct digitizing and processing of detector signals, {{have recently been}} favoured over analog electronics, ensuring higher flexibility, stability and lower dead time. We present our research activities {{on the development of}} X-ray and <b>gamma</b> <b>ray</b> <b>spectrometers</b> based on semiconductor detectors and DPP systems. We developed off-line and real-time DPP systems able to perform precise height and shape analysis of detector pulses. X-ray and <b>gamma</b> <b>ray</b> spectra measurements with cadmium telluride (CdTe) and germanium (Ge) detectors highlight the excellent performance of the systems both at low and high rate environments (up to 800 kcps) ...|$|R
